## Mode 2 design contract (frozen for this sprint)

| Aspect | Decision |
|---|---|
| Beat driver | GSAP timeline synced to BPM (reuse `useGameTimeline` pattern, not setInterval) |
| Hit window | ±200 ms around beat centre; early/late = wrong (same mistake counter) |
| Sequence length | 4 notes per round (configurable per sub-level) |
| Sub-levels | 3 tiers: BPM 72 / 96 / 120, note pool from L1→L3 |
| Visual path | Horizontal row of 4 note slots; active slot highlighted; mascot flies on beat advance |
| Timer ring | Shows progress **to next beat**, not whole sequence |
| Scoring | +10 per on-beat hit; streak multiplier preserved from Mode 1 |
| Game over | Same rule: 3 mistakes |

## Landscape layout contract (667×375)

| Element | Landscape rule |
|---|---|
| Score panel | Single compact row, `py-1`, smaller badge |
| Mascot | Max `64px` height in landscape; or inline left column |
| Note + ring | Max ring `80px`; VexFlow compact staff |
| Piano | Use `variant="compact"` or reduced octave span if needed |
| Start / GameOver | Side-by-side or stacked with `min()` clamps, no `text-5xl` |
| Safe area | Respect `env(safe-area-inset-*)` in landscape |

## Definition of Done
- Start screen offers **Find** and **Rhythm** mode buttons; each launches correct loop.
- Mode 1 behaviour unchanged (regression-safe).
- Mode 2: beat sequence playable end-to-end with mascot flight + beat timer.
- Chrome DevTools device `667×375` landscape: zero vertical scroll, no clipped CTAs.
- README section: modes explained + landscape testing note.
- `git commit` after each task.

## Risks
- Piano keyboard height dominates 375px — may require landscape-specific octave range (C4–B4).
- Rhythm audio sync: preload metronome click optional; reuse Tone.js tap on beat.
- `useGameEngine` vs separate hook: prefer **separate `useRhythmEngine`** to avoid breaking Mode 1.
